    <p><br>
    </p>
    <p style="text-align: center;"> </p>
    <p><br>
    </p>
    <p>If you haven't successfully programmed your Arduino yet, go back to the
      blink sketch and make it happen.</p>
    <p>In the Arduino IDE, install this library to drive the LED displays:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Tools-&gt;Manage Libraries - Fine MD_MAX72XX and click install</li>
    </ul>
    In the Arduino IDE, set up the hardware:
    <ul>
      <li>Tools-&gt;Board-&gt;Arduino Nano</li>
      <li>Tools-&gt;Processor-&gt;Atmega328P (Old Bootloader)</li>
      <li>Tools-&gt;Port-&gt; whatever port appears in this list when you plug
        in the Arduino</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Download, modify, compile and upload the sketch</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/KnoxMakers/Electronics/tree/master/UltiBadge/example_code/switch_test">Download
          switch_test,ino</a> from the KnoxMakers Github</li>
      <li>There are multiple ways that the LED modules are wired up. The code
        may need a modification for the display to orient characters correctly.
        At the top of the sketch there are a few lines that define this, read
        the associated comment and use trial and error to find out what works
        for you.</li>
      <li>Compile, upload and enjoy!</li>
    </ul>
    <br>
    <p><br>
    </p>
